1
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,040
President Wang.

2
00:01:36,239 --> 00:01:36,760
Director Zhou.

3
00:01:38,359 --> 00:01:38,760
Have a seat.

4
00:01:50,439 --> 00:01:50,879
Director Zhou,

5
00:01:52,959 --> 00:01:54,079
before I came here,

6
00:01:54,359 --> 00:01:55,239
I'd already heard

7
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:58,159
that Cardiology's acting director

8
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,159
is young and accomplished,

9
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:02,200
the youngest head

10
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,760
of a major department

11
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,200
in Dongjiang's entire

12
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,400
healthcare system

13
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,599
in the past decade.

14
00:02:09,159 --> 00:02:10,039
You're too kind, President Wang.

15
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:12,439
I've read your report.

16
00:02:12,639 --> 00:02:13,319
It's very well written.

17
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,680
You have clear ideas

18
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:17,319
about reform.

19
00:02:17,479 --> 00:02:18,199
Keep it up.

20
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,560
Thank you, President Wang.

21
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,479
About your proposal

22
00:02:22,719 --> 00:02:23,919
for a joint clinic,

23
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,520
President Cui

24
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,680
has mentioned it many times.

25
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,919
I've reviewed it carefully.

26
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,479
It's a very good idea.

27
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:33,719
However,

28
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,240
have you discussed

29
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,879
patient assignment and billing

30
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,080
with Director Sheng?

31
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,439
We're still waiting for his response.

32
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,719
On this matter,

33
00:02:45,719 --> 00:02:46,479
I think you should

34
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:47,639
listen to his views.

35
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,960
He's held the position longer

36
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,080
and has

37
00:02:51,319 --> 00:02:52,280
extensive management experience.

38
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:53,840
Understood.

39
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,319
At present,

40
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:56,960
Cardiology's workload

41
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,120
is acceptable,

42
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,280
but

43
00:02:59,759 --> 00:03:02,240
your spending is poorly controlled.

44
00:03:03,439 --> 00:03:05,039
Your average length of stay

45
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:06,199
exceeds the target.

46
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,240
I need to

47
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,319
specifically remind you of that.

48
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:10,080
That's mainly because

49
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,879
of the prolonged heat wave in August.

50
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,199
We admitted

51
00:03:12,199 --> 00:03:12,800
more coronary patients,

52
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:14,400
and our patients

53
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,159
are mostly elderly with chronic illnesses.

54
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:18,080
You don't need to explain.

55
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,800
If the other departments can do it,

56
00:03:20,039 --> 00:03:21,240
if your mentor could do it,

57
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,879
and your predecessor could do it,

58
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,360
then so should you.

59
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:25,680
I'm not someone

60
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:28,039
who wants to hear excuses.

61
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,639
Another thing:

62
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,199
you proposed

63
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,560
supporting lower-level hospitals

64
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,120
and improving benefits

65
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:35,719
for younger doctors.

66
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,439
I have no objection to that.

67
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,360
But

68
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,879
as department director,

69
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,759
your first priority

70
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:43,919
must be the department's growth.

71
00:03:44,439 --> 00:03:46,120
All your current expenses

72
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:47,319
come from

73
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,439
the department's overall budget.

74
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,680
Your reserves aren't that strong.

75
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:53,479
If you keep spending like this,

76
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,400
cash flow will become tight.

77
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,520
Your task now,

78
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,719
in my opinion,

79
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,439
is to increase revenue and cut costs.

80
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,879
Understood, President Wang.

81
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:14,199
You went from

82
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,879
head of the coronary team

83
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,240
to acting director.

84
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:20,560
That was already

85
00:04:20,639 --> 00:04:22,199
an exceptional promotion.

86
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,120
Now that you're in this position,

87
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:27,079
I hope, in time,

88
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:13,800
you'll show me

89
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:14,639
what you're truly capable of.

90
00:06:16,399 --> 00:06:17,240
Why do you think Zhou called us in?

91
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:18,839
To discuss

92
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,720
how we should work going forward

93
00:06:21,199 --> 00:06:23,199
and remind us he's the acting director.

94
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,480
Sharp as ever, Brother Zhan.

95
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,120
The moment he arrived,

96
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,519
he raised subsidies for young doctors

97
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:32,120
and sent staff and equipment to Guizhou.

98
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,040
Did he discuss

99
00:06:33,079 --> 00:06:34,240
any of that with us beforehand?

100
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:35,279
Exactly.

101
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,560
Now that he wants to make his presence felt,

102
00:06:36,639 --> 00:06:37,800
he suddenly remembers to consult us.

103
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,560
Come on, look at this.

104
00:06:42,759 --> 00:06:44,160
Doesn't this person look like him?

105
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:45,800
This is from

106
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,759
my son's class parent group.

107
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:47,639
One parent

108
00:06:47,759 --> 00:06:48,920
wants to give the teacher a gift,

109
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,360
but she wants all of us

110
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:51,800
to split the cost.

111
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,800
Why should we?

112
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:54,040
Isn't that emotional blackmail?

113
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:54,680
Right?

114
00:06:55,199 --> 00:06:56,600
She gets all the credit,

115
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,839
and we foot the bill.

116
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:58,519
Doesn't that sound like him?

117
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,480
I'm telling you, even their faces look alike.

118
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:01,079
Look closely.

119
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:01,519
Director.

120
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,800
That's a bit much.

121
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,079
Director.

122
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:17,439
Sorry to keep you waiting.

123
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,920
Here's the situation.

124
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:21,360
I've reviewed the data

125
00:07:21,879 --> 00:07:23,120
and found that our department's

126
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,279
average length of stay this year

127
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:26,399
has increased

128
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,800
by 2.2 days year-on-year.

129
00:07:28,319 --> 00:07:29,199
That exceeds

130
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,120
the hospital's target.

131
00:07:30,439 --> 00:07:31,079
And this month,

132
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,160
it is still trending upward.

133
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:34,279
As you all know,

134
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,879
a low bed turnover rate

135
00:07:36,279 --> 00:07:37,240
directly affects

136
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,360
our department's performance bonus.

137
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:43,120
Director,

138
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,439
we can't help

139
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,600
the longer average stay.

140
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,160
We have too many elderly patients.

141
00:07:48,839 --> 00:07:50,560
They stay for over ten days and tie up beds.

142
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,040
I think

143
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,199
some patients shouldn't be admitted.

144
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,680
Take Yu Aizhu, for example.

145
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:56,800
That bed

146
00:07:57,399 --> 00:07:58,199
should be reserved

147
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,360
for patients with better prospects.

148
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,279
You can't put it that way.

149
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,560
Elderly people still need treatment.

150
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,279
Exactly.

151
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,000
We can't openly cherry-pick patients.

152
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:10,839
In my view,

153
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,079
the real issue is cooperation.

154
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:14,279
Right.

155
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:15,519
Actually...

156
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:18,959
It's all right, Director Hong.

157
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:20,759
Say whatever's on your mind.

158
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:23,240
Director,

159
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,160
before you went to Guizhou,

160
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:27,439
Cardiology as a whole

161
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,319
was on an upward trajectory.

162
00:08:31,199 --> 00:08:32,759
President Cui strongly backed us,

163
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,519
and Director Jiang in Cardiac Surgery

164
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,960
was generous and supportive.

165
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,799
So the two departments

166
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:39,000
worked very well together.

167
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,440
For many high-risk interventions,

168
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,519
we only dared to proceed

169
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,720
because Cardiac Surgery had our backs.

170
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,279
Only by doing advanced procedures

171
00:08:45,679 --> 00:08:47,000
can we build our reputation.

172
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:48,480
But after Director Jiang retired,

173
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:50,000
Cardiac Surgery

174
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:52,000
became harder to mobilize.

175
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,480
Now that President Cui is leaving,

176
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,279
I'm afraid, going forward...

177
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,559
Exactly.

178
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,279
Not everyone

179
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,399
has your relationship

180
00:08:58,399 --> 00:08:59,360
with Lin Yi.

181
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,360
And I've heard

182
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:04,399
the new President Wang

183
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,080
values social responsibility,

184
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,759
but also stresses financial returns.

185
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:09,080
Director Sheng is his former student.

186
00:09:10,399 --> 00:09:12,720
Back at Third Hospital,

187
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,960
Director Sheng

188
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:16,960
strongly promoted valve interventions.

189
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,720
If they take

190
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,120
that business too,

191
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:22,240
our performance bonuses

192
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:23,679
will suffer even more.

193
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,480
In the future,

194
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,480
even if all of us team leaders

195
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:27,240
gave up our entire bonuses,

196
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,879
it still wouldn't

197
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,279
fill the gap.

198
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,000
So,

199
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,600
Director Zhou,

200
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:35,120
we're all counting on you.

201
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:38,840
When the time comes,

202
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,120
do what needs to be done.

203
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,519
Where did Dong's go?

204
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,639
I didn't see it. Did you?

205
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,120
It's here.

206
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:01,519
Up there.

207
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,840
Hu Weiping, where's the proposal?

208
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:03,679
Where is it?

209
00:10:03,679 --> 00:10:04,320
I really...

210
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,039
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

211
00:10:05,159 --> 00:10:06,120
Why are you so careless?

212
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,159
It's not that I don't care.

213
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:07,960
I already finished it.

214
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,200
Please put your bag through security.

215
00:10:09,519 --> 00:10:10,240
I only stepped out for a cigarette.

216
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:10,919
I already had it checked.

217
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,879
Sorry, sir.

218
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:12,919
All bags must go through.

219
00:10:12,919 --> 00:10:13,720
Mr. Su, that's not what happened.

220
00:10:13,799 --> 00:10:14,799
I finished it this morning.

221
00:10:14,799 --> 00:10:15,159
Enough.

222
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:15,600
Stop explaining.

223
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:16,759
I don't want to hear it.

224
00:10:16,759 --> 00:10:18,080
If you can't do the job, leave.

225
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:18,559
Hello?

226
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,720
All bags through security, please.

227
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,000
Sir.

228
00:10:25,159 --> 00:10:26,120
I've told you several times.

229
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:27,240
Your bag has to be scanned.

230
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:30,519
Here.

231
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,000
Go ahead, look.

232
00:10:32,039 --> 00:10:33,200
I can't. The machine has to.

233
00:10:33,879 --> 00:10:34,480
Fine. Let the machine look.

234
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:35,639
Look.

235
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:36,840
At what?

236
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,840
See if there's a weapon in there,

237
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,679
one that can kill you or me.

238
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:41,840
Watch your mouth.

239
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:43,159
It was only one cigarette.

240
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:43,600
Is this really necessary?

241
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,480
It's our policy.

242
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:46,600
Stop arguing.

243
00:10:47,519 --> 00:10:48,399
Are you the patient's family?

244
00:10:48,519 --> 00:10:49,879
Aren't these all the stupid forms?

245
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,679
Payment slip, admission papers, medical records.

246
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,559
What else?

247
00:10:52,759 --> 00:10:54,080
What else am I missing?

248
00:10:57,679 --> 00:10:58,559
Move along.

249
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,440
Nothing to see.

250
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:00,559
Stop filming.

251
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,279
No photos.

252
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:03,080
Everyone, go back.

253
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,279
Is everything there?

254
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:15,559
I'm sorry.

255
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,840
Sometimes an adult can fall apart

256
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:36,960
in a single instant.

257
00:11:38,679 --> 00:11:39,879
Didn't you see?

258
00:11:40,679 --> 00:11:41,759
He feels guilty

259
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:42,600
and has nowhere to vent it.

260
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,360
What do you mean?

261
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,679
He can't take much more.

262
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,039
I think

263
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,120
he wants to give up.

264
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:50,759
He's truly ready to give up.

265
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,320
But...

266
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,159
with either Director Lin

267
00:11:53,159 --> 00:11:54,159
or Director Zhou operating,

268
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:54,960
the surgery

269
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,720
should succeed.

270
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,320
You still don't understand.

271
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:59,080
What they need now

272
00:11:59,080 --> 00:11:59,919
is someone to decide for them,

273
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,440
or clearly tell them,

274
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,919
"Give up. There's no hope."

275
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,159
That would ease

276
00:12:04,159 --> 00:12:05,240
the guilt they feel.

277
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:07,840
I just can't imagine

278
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,639
her own son

279
00:12:08,679 --> 00:12:09,480
and her own husband...

280
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:11,399
I can't understand it.

281
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:12,559
And what does that change?

282
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:14,759
The cost is one issue.

283
00:12:15,559 --> 00:12:16,799
Another is that they're exhausted.

284
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,000
You saw it yourself.

285
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,200
Why do you only sympathize with the patient,

286
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,559
not the family?

287
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,399
And often,

288
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,399
during treatment,

289
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:24,480
the patient suffers too.

290
00:12:25,759 --> 00:12:26,639
I'll say it again:

291
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,960
Don't judge pain you've never endured.

292
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,639
But...

293
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:33,440
Xiao Gu,

294
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:34,960
take the patient back to the ward.

295
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,159
Tell the family the surgery went well.

296
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,440
I'll speak with them shortly.

297
00:12:38,039 --> 00:12:38,600
Yes, Director.

298
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:39,519
By the way, Director,

299
00:12:39,879 --> 00:12:40,679
I spoke again this morning

300
00:12:40,679 --> 00:12:42,080
with Yu Aizhu's family.

301
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,240
I explained in detail

302
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:43,879
the possibility of transfemoral

303
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:44,320
transcatheter aortic valve replacement.

304
00:12:44,519 --> 00:12:45,240
I told them

305
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,039
the procedure carries risks,

306
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,120
but it's worth trying.

307
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,399
Yet they still

308
00:12:50,639 --> 00:12:51,639
can't make up their minds.

309
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,840
Her son doesn't live in Dongjiang.

310
00:12:53,919 --> 00:12:54,840
On one hand, he worries

311
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,639
about putting his father through more.

312
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,600
On the other,

313
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,279
he's afraid his mother will suffer.

314
00:12:58,679 --> 00:12:59,639
How is the patient?

315
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:00,639
Fairly stable.

316
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,919
She no longer recognizes

317
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,080
her own family,

318
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,039
but sometimes she still knows

319
00:13:05,039 --> 00:13:05,759
that I'm her doctor.

320
00:13:06,159 --> 00:13:07,600
She's cooperative with medication and injections.

321
00:13:08,039 --> 00:13:09,440
She still has the instinct to survive.

322
00:13:09,919 --> 00:13:10,799
With Alzheimer's disease

323
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:11,720
at her stage,

324
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:12,440
she is essentially

325
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:13,559
legally incapable of making decisions.

326
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,799
Her treatment plan

327
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,720
can only be decided by her guardian.

328
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,159
If the guardian declines treatment,

329
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:18,840
there's little we can do.

330
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,480
Beds are extremely tight.

331
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:22,000
Many patients are waiting.

332
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,240
Confirm with them one more time.

333
00:13:27,039 --> 00:13:28,360
If they truly refuse treatment,

334
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:29,679
we can only discharge her.

335
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:30,480
Okay.

336
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:38,399
I understand.

337
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:39,879
ER has a patient

338
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:40,879
with a cerebral hemorrhage and heart attack.

339
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:41,600
They're transferring him now.

340
00:13:42,039 --> 00:13:42,559
Director,

341
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,159
you've already done three surgeries straight.

342
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:44,960
I'll find another...

343
00:13:45,039 --> 00:13:46,120
Go speak with Yu Aizhu's family.

344
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:52,240
We can remove the nasal oxygen

345
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,360
and let her rest.

346
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,519
Director Lin.

347
00:13:56,159 --> 00:13:56,799
Where is her family?

348
00:13:57,519 --> 00:13:58,279
They're discussing

349
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,240
the treatment plan with Dr. Zhang.

350
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,240
All right.

351
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,399
You're done here. Leave this to me.

352
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:04,919
Thank you, Director Lin.

353
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,759
Little Turtle,

354
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,600
how are you feeling today?

355
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,279
I'm Little Rabbit.

356
00:14:18,519 --> 00:14:19,240
Lin Rabbit.

357
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,879
Lin Yi.

358
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,120
You recognized me.

359
00:14:33,159 --> 00:14:34,600
Pingzi is outside.

360
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,960
He hasn't gone to school yet.

361
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:41,360
I'll go downstairs

362
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:42,919
after he leaves.

363
00:14:47,399 --> 00:14:48,039
Why?

364
00:14:49,519 --> 00:14:51,200
I cut my hair.

365
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,399
I don't want him to see it.

366
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,320
My hair

367
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,559
was long,

368
00:15:04,919 --> 00:15:05,879
black,

369
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,080
and thick.

370
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,960
I cut it off

371
00:15:13,159 --> 00:15:13,919
and sold it.

372
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,919
I got eighty yuan.

373
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,759
Impressive, right?

374
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:24,919
Why did you sell your hair?

375
00:15:26,399 --> 00:15:28,559
To order milk for Pingzi.

376
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,440
He's taking his high school entrance exam.

377
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:33,840
He needs good nutrition.

378
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:37,240
An egg and a glass of milk every morning

379
00:15:37,279 --> 00:15:38,480
are essential.

380
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,039
We ran out of money.

381
00:15:43,039 --> 00:15:45,000
So I took scissors,

382
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:53,960
cut off my hair,

383
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,080
and sold it.

384
00:15:58,519 --> 00:15:59,000
I...

385
00:15:59,879 --> 00:16:01,240
don't want him to see me.

386
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,320
I look so ugly.

387
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,360
It doesn't look good.

388
00:16:05,879 --> 00:16:06,720
You're not ugly.

389
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:08,879
Not at all.

390
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,320
Your face is beautiful.

391
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,279
You look good with long or short hair.

392
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:22,720
Little Rabbit.

393
00:16:25,759 --> 00:16:26,480
That's right.

394
00:16:26,799 --> 00:16:28,519
I'm Little Rabbit, Little Turtle.

395
00:16:31,919 --> 00:16:32,720
Now,

396
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,080
Pingzi

397
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,320
has gone out.

398
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,720
So, Little Turtle,

399
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,159
do you want to race

400
00:16:39,519 --> 00:16:40,639
Little Rabbit again?

401
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,080
Little Turtle is tired.

402
00:16:50,559 --> 00:16:51,559
Little Turtle

403
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:53,679
can't run anymore.

404
00:16:55,559 --> 00:16:56,639
She's too slow now.

405
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,960
Little Turtle is tired.

406
00:17:05,039 --> 00:17:06,960
She wants to run, but can't.

407
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,640
She can't run fast anymore.

408
00:17:12,759 --> 00:17:13,599
Pingzi.

409
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,279
Pingzi, drink your milk.

410
00:17:18,039 --> 00:17:20,119
Mom ordered it for you.

411
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,880
Drink your milk.

412
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:27,880
Mom already ordered it.

413
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,559
We've decided.

414
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:37,160
We'll...

415
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:40,160
choose

416
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:42,839
conservative treatment.

417
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:44,839
Are you sure?

418
00:17:54,319 --> 00:17:55,200
If you've decided

419
00:17:55,799 --> 00:17:56,480
against any further

420
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,519
surgical treatment,

421
00:17:59,359 --> 00:18:01,279
we'll have to discharge her.

422
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:05,519
Could...

423
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,000
could you let her

424
00:18:08,039 --> 00:18:09,039
stay two more days?

425
00:18:09,079 --> 00:18:09,799
I...

426
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:11,880
I'll try to find

427
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,880
a nursing home for Mom.

428
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,000
Hospital beds are extremely tight.

429
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,680
Patients awaiting surgery

430
00:18:19,039 --> 00:18:19,960
are still in line.

431
00:18:21,079 --> 00:18:22,519
Aunt Yu's condition

432
00:18:22,599 --> 00:18:24,559
is currently stable.

433
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:28,480
Let's discharge her.

434
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,799
We'll go home first.

435
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,240
But Dad, you...

436
00:18:36,359 --> 00:18:38,119
you haven't fully recovered.

437
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:44,559
With conservative treatment,

438
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,559
you can transfer her

439
00:18:45,559 --> 00:18:46,200
to a lower-level hospital.

440
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,839
If you need,

441
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,240
I can recommend one.

442
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,440
That works.

443
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,160
It's still better than home.

444
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:56,319
Okay.

445
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,319
I'll make the arrangements.

446
00:18:59,079 --> 00:19:00,039
If later

447
00:19:00,359 --> 00:19:01,359
you decide to let Aunt Yu

448
00:19:01,359 --> 00:19:02,119
have the surgery,

449
00:19:02,319 --> 00:19:03,119
you can come back anytime.

450
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,000
All right?

451
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:05,400
Okay.

452
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,319
Thank you, Dr. Zhang.

453
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:11,200
Let's go.

454
00:19:34,759 --> 00:19:35,559
Dad,

455
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,799
why don't you return to your ward?

456
00:19:36,839 --> 00:19:37,559
I'll go pay the bill.

457
00:19:37,559 --> 00:19:38,519
I'll go see Mom.

458
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:39,759
No need.

459
00:19:42,359 --> 00:19:43,200
I'll go see her.

460
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,519
I'll comb her hair.

461
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,359
Make it look nice.

462
00:20:00,839 --> 00:20:02,960
Make her beautiful.

463
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,680
We'll go home in a few days.

464
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,160
Braid it.

465
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:07,720
Okay.

466
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,400
A big braid.

467
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,920
Yes, a big braid.

468
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:11,279
Okay.

469
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,680
Beautiful.

470
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,759
We'll go home in a few days.

471
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:15,559
Okay.

472
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:20,079
Your hair

473
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,359
looks beautiful.

474
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:43,599
Mom.

475
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,559
She's coughing.

476
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,279
Come on, Mom. Spit it out.

477
00:20:55,759 --> 00:20:56,680
Mom's coughing.

478
00:20:59,079 --> 00:21:00,000
Pingzi.

479
00:21:01,119 --> 00:21:02,200
It's not even dawn yet.

480
00:21:02,279 --> 00:21:03,119
Sleep a little longer, Mom.

481
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,079
Everyone's asleep.

482
00:21:04,519 --> 00:21:06,160
Why haven't you shaved?

483
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,440
Mom.

484
00:21:15,119 --> 00:21:16,480
Mom, do you...

485
00:21:16,519 --> 00:21:17,559
Mom, you recognize me?

486
00:21:19,079 --> 00:21:21,039
My Pingzi has lost weight.

487
00:21:23,319 --> 00:21:23,880
Mom.

488
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,400
Mom!

489
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:27,720
Mom, who am I?

490
00:21:29,319 --> 00:21:30,720
Pingzi.

491
00:21:34,519 --> 00:21:35,759
Even if work is busy,

492
00:21:37,039 --> 00:21:38,720
you must eat properly.

493
00:21:39,559 --> 00:21:40,279
Mom.

494
00:21:41,559 --> 00:21:42,279
Are you hungry?

495
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,119
I'll cook noodles for you.

496
00:21:47,039 --> 00:21:48,359
Fresh noodles

497
00:21:49,279 --> 00:21:51,400
go into boiling water.

498
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,960
Dried noodles...

499
00:21:54,519 --> 00:21:55,640
Dried noodles

500
00:21:56,319 --> 00:21:57,960
go in when small bubbles appear.

501
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:02,400
That's how noodles taste best.

502
00:22:03,799 --> 00:22:05,799
Fresh noodles go into boiling water.

503
00:22:08,079 --> 00:22:08,799
For dried noodles,

504
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,480
put them in when small bubbles appear.

505
00:22:11,119 --> 00:22:12,839
That's how they taste best.

506
00:22:14,759 --> 00:22:15,480
Remember?

507
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,440
I remember.

508
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,319
Our Pingzi

509
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:22,440
loves them most.

510
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,160
Mom,

511
00:22:23,519 --> 00:22:24,279
your noodles

512
00:22:24,559 --> 00:22:25,960
are the best in the world.

513
00:22:26,119 --> 00:22:26,960
Silly boy.

514
00:22:28,799 --> 00:22:29,559
Cooking noodles for you

515
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,599
is also the happiest thing

516
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:31,400
in the world for Mom.

517
00:22:34,359 --> 00:22:36,680
Do you know our Pingzi?

518
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,279
Ask him to bring you here.

519
00:22:42,519 --> 00:22:43,480
No.

520
00:22:44,519 --> 00:22:45,400
No.

521
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,839
Pingzi is too busy.

522
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,240
He doesn't have time to see me.

523
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:53,720
Don't bother Pingzi.

524
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,640
Pingzi.

525
00:22:56,839 --> 00:22:58,640
Pingzi.

526
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,799
Pingzi.

527
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,640
Pingzi.

528
00:23:06,079 --> 00:23:07,359
Pingzi...

529
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,200
Dad.

530
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:13,960
Maybe we should do the surgery.

531
00:23:14,799 --> 00:23:16,359
Mom recognized me yesterday.

532
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,119
She still knows me.

533
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,079
I don't want to just watch her

534
00:23:23,839 --> 00:23:24,880
wait to die.

535
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:28,839
Forget it.

536
00:23:31,279 --> 00:23:32,319
Don't put her through more.

537
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,720
Seventy is already a long life.

538
00:23:37,039 --> 00:23:37,599
Dad,

539
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,319
I know these years

540
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,880
have been incredibly hard for you.

541
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:44,920
How about this?

542
00:23:45,559 --> 00:23:47,279
After she recovers from surgery,

543
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:49,000
I'll take both of you to Shenzhen.

544
00:23:49,079 --> 00:23:49,720
We'll live together.

545
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:50,680
We'll care for Mom together.

546
00:23:51,039 --> 00:23:52,079
Your place in Shenzhen

547
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,079
only has two bedrooms.

548
00:23:54,279 --> 00:23:55,559
Where would we stay?

549
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,960
We're family.

550
00:23:59,519 --> 00:24:01,000
We can make it work.

551
00:24:01,359 --> 00:24:02,799
As long as she's alive,

552
00:24:03,599 --> 00:24:04,240
I still...

553
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,279
still have a mother.

554
00:24:06,119 --> 00:24:07,079
I can still be

555
00:24:07,079 --> 00:24:08,279
someone's child.

556
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:11,519
I don't agree.

557
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:12,759
You finally

558
00:24:12,759 --> 00:24:13,960
built a home in Shenzhen.

559
00:24:14,599 --> 00:24:16,440
If your mother and I move in,

560
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,039
especially in her condition,

561
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:19,880
son,

562
00:24:20,279 --> 00:24:21,440
will you ever

563
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,000
have a peaceful life

564
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:23,759
again?

565
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:29,559
And Dabao

566
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:32,920
is starting middle school soon.

567
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:34,759
He needs

568
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:36,640
a good study environment.

569
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,160
But I'm

570
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,279
her only son.

571
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,400
She treasured me since childhood.

572
00:24:44,839 --> 00:24:45,640
When you were laid off

573
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:46,680
and things were hardest,

574
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,240
she sold her hair

575
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:48,799
just to buy me milk.

576
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,279
She cared so much about looking good.

577
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:52,839
Look at her now.

578
00:24:53,519 --> 00:24:55,200
She can still be treated.

579
00:24:55,519 --> 00:24:56,279
There's still hope.

580
00:24:56,599 --> 00:24:57,519
If we stop,

581
00:24:58,759 --> 00:24:59,240
Dad,

582
00:24:59,519 --> 00:24:59,960
am I...

583
00:25:00,839 --> 00:25:02,160
am I even human?

584
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:03,799
Don't talk nonsense.

585
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:06,759
No one will blame you.

586
00:25:07,319 --> 00:25:08,559
Your mother recognizing you yesterday

587
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,279
was only a brief lucid moment.

588
00:25:11,359 --> 00:25:13,000
She keeps calling me Pingzi.

589
00:25:14,359 --> 00:25:15,599
Did she recognize you this morning?

590
00:25:18,799 --> 00:25:19,400
Son,

591
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,759
don't torture yourself.

592
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,839
Even if your mother were lucid,

593
00:25:27,319 --> 00:25:28,799
she wouldn't blame you.

594
00:25:31,079 --> 00:25:32,559
I can't live with it.

595
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,759
I can't get past

596
00:25:35,799 --> 00:25:36,680
this.

597
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:43,680
Then maybe we...

598
00:25:45,359 --> 00:25:47,000
I'll sell the Shenzhen apartment

599
00:25:47,559 --> 00:25:49,039
and bring my wife and child back.

600
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,799
Stop saying things in anger.

601
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,200
Look at your mother

602
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,200
as she is now.

603
00:25:56,319 --> 00:25:58,519
Even if the surgery succeeds,

604
00:25:58,839 --> 00:25:59,759
she still won't have

605
00:25:59,839 --> 00:26:01,559
much quality of life.

606
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,680
At this stage of life,

607
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:10,440
parents survive

608
00:26:11,079 --> 00:26:11,880
by draining

609
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,480
their children.

610
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:17,839
I've spent my whole life

611
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:19,599
worn down by her illness.

612
00:26:21,279 --> 00:26:23,039
I won't let her ruin you too.

613
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,799
But she's my mother.

614
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:31,440
I have a duty to her.

615
00:26:32,079 --> 00:26:33,440
I know she's your mother.

616
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,839
This decision is mine,

617
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,000
not yours.

618
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,160
I'll give everything I have

619
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,920
to stay with her.

620
00:26:42,079 --> 00:26:43,759
I'll make sure she leaves

621
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:44,839
clean and with dignity.

622
00:26:50,599 --> 00:26:51,880
Go look at your mother.

623
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,480
She's been bedridden over a year.

624
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:56,680
Does she have a single bedsore?

625
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:00,359
All right, here we go.

626
00:27:00,839 --> 00:27:02,240
Come on. Stop tapping.

627
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,279
Let's wipe your hand.

628
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,119
Wipe your hand.

629
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,000
Smells nice.

630
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:11,519
You know

631
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,440
your mother likes being clean.

632
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,079
I wipe and wash her every day

633
00:27:17,119 --> 00:27:18,319
and keep her clean.

634
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:22,720
Okay.

635
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,599
Slowly.

636
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,400
Slow down.

637
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:24,880
Easy.

638
00:27:28,039 --> 00:27:28,519
All right.

639
00:27:30,039 --> 00:27:31,319
I told you to slow down.

640
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,839
Why are you going so fast?

641
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:33,359
Seriously.

642
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:35,200
Come on.

643
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:36,480
Come on.

644
00:27:37,039 --> 00:27:38,279
Lift up. Take it out.

645
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:38,799
Come on.

646
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:39,599
Lift it.

647
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:40,720
Hold it up.

648
00:27:41,799 --> 00:27:42,839
Work with me now,

649
00:27:43,279 --> 00:27:44,680
and it'll be much easier.

650
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,200
Understand?

651
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:46,279
All right.

652
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,119
I've done right by her, haven't I?

653
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:54,519
Dad, don't cry.

654
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:58,839
I've honored

655
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,079
the decades of love

656
00:28:00,119 --> 00:28:01,599
between us, haven't I?

657
00:28:06,599 --> 00:28:08,599
I've done right by you too, son.

658
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:12,480
In any case,

659
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,640
my conscience is clear.

660
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:20,559
If I ever end up like this,

661
00:28:21,599 --> 00:28:23,519
don't spend money saving me.

662
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,759
Let me go with dignity.

663
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:28,160
I'd thank you for it.

664
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:31,759
Don't say that.

665
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:35,519
Pingzi.

666
00:28:36,319 --> 00:28:37,480
Pingzi.

667
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:38,799
Pingzi.

668
00:28:38,799 --> 00:28:39,279
I'll go.

669
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:52,559
See?

670
00:28:58,079 --> 00:28:58,640
So

671
00:29:00,319 --> 00:29:01,319
it had no effect at all.

672
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:04,160
That's enough.

673
00:29:04,759 --> 00:29:05,440
Come on, sit up.

674
00:29:09,559 --> 00:29:10,519
If he asks when he comes out,

675
00:29:10,559 --> 00:29:12,039
don't answer. Let me.

676
00:29:14,759 --> 00:29:15,279
How is it?

677
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,119
Right now,

678
00:29:17,519 --> 00:29:18,880
we still can't see clearly,

679
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:19,880
but it looks fairly good.

680
00:29:20,079 --> 00:29:20,440
Right?

681
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:22,000
Send the data

682
00:29:22,039 --> 00:29:22,920
to Hainan later

683
00:29:23,319 --> 00:29:24,000
and let us review it again.

684
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:24,759
Then we'll decide the next treatment.

685
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:26,480
Really?

686
00:29:27,359 --> 00:29:27,799
All right.

687
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,200
Next time we go to Hainan,

688
00:29:29,599 --> 00:29:30,640
let's eat at that coconut chicken place.

689
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:31,759
Sure.

690
00:29:33,039 --> 00:29:34,000
Thank you, Xiao Qin.

691
00:29:34,039 --> 00:29:34,559
We'll get going. Thank you.

692
00:29:34,559 --> 00:29:34,960
No problem.

693
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,079
Take care.

694
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,039
You know Director Lin's nephew, Xiaorui?

695
00:29:52,319 --> 00:29:52,839
Right?

696
00:29:53,319 --> 00:29:53,920
Recently,

697
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,240
he tried a new stem-cell therapy.

698
00:29:55,559 --> 00:29:57,079
But there was no real improvement.

699
00:29:57,279 --> 00:29:58,359
Director Lin still doesn't dare tell him.

700
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,519
That's heartbreaking.

701
00:30:00,559 --> 00:30:01,599
Yeah. Such a shame.

702
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:03,359
Don't tell anyone.

703
00:30:03,839 --> 00:30:04,279
Don't worry.

704
00:30:20,519 --> 00:30:21,559
Where should we go

705
00:30:21,559 --> 00:30:22,319
for family day this week?

706
00:30:23,519 --> 00:30:24,480
The botanical garden?

707
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,039
Plants versus Zombies!

708
00:30:26,559 --> 00:30:27,519
The botanical garden again?

709
00:30:27,559 --> 00:30:28,920
Didn't we go last month?

710
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:30,599
We did.

711
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:31,960
Then let's go to the zoo.

712
00:30:32,599 --> 00:30:33,759
We can visit

713
00:30:33,839 --> 00:30:35,119
the big bear you adopted,

714
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,240
and also get

715
00:30:36,279 --> 00:30:36,839
Xiaorui's favorite:

716
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:37,640
noodles with gravy and a chicken leg.

717
00:30:37,839 --> 00:30:38,839
Eryi, turn on the lights.

718
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:40,519
I'm fine with that.

719
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,480
What does Xiaorui think?

720
00:30:42,839 --> 00:30:43,839
This week...

721
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:46,319
I don't really want to go out.

722
00:30:46,559 --> 00:30:47,480
I want to stay home.

723
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:50,640
That's fine.

724
00:30:51,039 --> 00:30:52,039
We'll stay home this weekend

725
00:30:52,079 --> 00:30:53,000
and make you something good.

726
00:30:55,559 --> 00:30:55,920
Okay.

727
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,160
Little Turtle.

728
00:31:17,039 --> 00:31:17,400
Here.

729
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:18,799
Write with this.

730
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,039
Old Hu,

731
00:31:25,599 --> 00:31:26,359
have you made a decision

732
00:31:26,359 --> 00:31:26,880
about the surgery?

733
00:31:27,039 --> 00:31:27,519
Director Lin.

734
00:31:30,519 --> 00:31:31,519
Whether Cardiology or Cardiac Surgery,

735
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:32,880
we'll do everything we can.

736
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,759
We've decided to leave tomorrow.

737
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:40,480
Why?

738
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,759
She can't keep staying here.

739
00:31:42,799 --> 00:31:43,519
It isn't right.

740
00:31:44,759 --> 00:31:46,480
We don't want to keep

741
00:31:46,519 --> 00:31:47,279
troubling the doctors and nurses.

742
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,599
Doctors and nurses would never see

743
00:31:53,599 --> 00:31:54,640
a patient as a burden.

744
00:31:57,599 --> 00:31:58,200
Is it...

745
00:31:58,559 --> 00:31:59,839
your son who wants to give up?

746
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,200
I'm the one giving up.

747
00:32:07,359 --> 00:32:08,559
If she keeps staying here,

748
00:32:09,279 --> 00:32:10,119
so many patients

749
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,519
are waiting for surgery.

750
00:32:12,279 --> 00:32:13,160
She'd be taking their bed.

751
00:32:19,559 --> 00:32:20,480
Aunt Yu's condition

752
00:32:20,559 --> 00:32:21,599
is too dangerous for discharge

753
00:32:21,799 --> 00:32:23,119
without surgery.

754
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,039
I once saw a video

755
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,400
while scrolling on my phone.

756
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,200
When elephants grow old

757
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,079
and can no longer care for themselves,

758
00:32:37,519 --> 00:32:38,519
they leave their young

759
00:32:38,599 --> 00:32:39,480
and find somewhere

760
00:32:39,599 --> 00:32:41,759
to quietly die alone.

761
00:32:44,079 --> 00:32:46,680
I couldn't understand it then.

762
00:32:49,039 --> 00:32:50,599
Now I see how helpless it is.

763
00:32:52,119 --> 00:32:52,799
When people grow old,

764
00:32:54,119 --> 00:32:55,759
they can't help their children

765
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,759
and only become a burden.

766
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:04,759
Come on, spit it out.

767
00:33:08,279 --> 00:33:09,720
Old Hu, don't be so pessimistic.

768
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:13,920
I'm only half joking,

769
00:33:15,359 --> 00:33:16,880
but sometimes she wears me down so much

770
00:33:17,559 --> 00:33:18,839
that I truly want

771
00:33:18,839 --> 00:33:19,960
to die with her.

772
00:33:24,519 --> 00:33:25,319
I remember

773
00:33:26,519 --> 00:33:28,519
the day she married me.

774
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:32,960
She sat behind her brother

775
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,720
on his bicycle,

776
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,279
wearing a red scarf,

777
00:33:38,119 --> 00:33:39,039
and her face

778
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,720
glowed bright red.

779
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,640
It feels like yesterday.

780
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,200
In the blink of an eye,

781
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,720
a whole lifetime has passed.

782
00:34:20,519 --> 00:34:21,880
I understand how you feel.

783
00:34:24,119 --> 00:34:25,039
When I was very young,

784
00:34:25,119 --> 00:34:26,119
my father died.

785
00:34:29,519 --> 00:34:30,360
Two years ago,

786
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,159
my brother passed away too.

787
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:41,199
But I still cherish

788
00:34:41,239 --> 00:34:42,599
his final days.

789
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:46,840
I read poetry to him,

790
00:34:51,039 --> 00:34:52,159
grew flowers with him,

791
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:57,519
and took photos.

792
00:34:59,039 --> 00:35:00,199
I still think,

793
00:35:02,519 --> 00:35:03,920
if only he were still here.

794
00:35:09,559 --> 00:35:10,159
Once someone is gone,

795
00:35:12,199 --> 00:35:13,400
they never come back.

796
00:35:16,599 --> 00:35:17,320
While she's still here,

797
00:35:19,119 --> 00:35:20,440
at least you can see her

798
00:35:21,599 --> 00:35:22,400
and touch her.

799
00:35:24,079 --> 00:35:25,360
That's already something to envy.

800
00:35:28,199 --> 00:35:29,400
Take care of yourself too.

801
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,039
You haven't fully recovered.

802
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,199
Don't let the wind hit you.

803
00:35:33,239 --> 00:35:34,000
Close the window.

804
00:35:38,039 --> 00:35:39,559
When will you be back?

805
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:47,079
She's very busy.

806
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:50,960
Please help me find a solution.

807
00:35:51,239 --> 00:35:51,800
My schedule

808
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,840
is packed this semester.

809
00:35:55,639 --> 00:35:56,800
I really can't manage it all.

810
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,239
At least don't assign me

811
00:35:59,239 --> 00:36:00,039
the basic courses.

812
00:36:00,599 --> 00:36:01,039
All right?

813
00:36:01,079 --> 00:36:01,480
Okay.

814
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:02,159
Thank you.

815
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:05,800
Yu Aizhu in Bed 10

816
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,000
is being discharged. Did you know?

817
00:36:07,599 --> 00:36:08,920
I heard she refused surgery.

818
00:36:10,599 --> 00:36:11,320
What do you mean, "heard"?

819
00:36:12,519 --> 00:36:13,519
Do you know or not?

820
00:36:14,079 --> 00:36:14,760
I know.

821
00:36:15,239 --> 00:36:16,280
Dr. Zhang is in charge of her.

822
00:36:16,559 --> 00:36:17,760
He must have explained everything carefully.

823
00:36:18,679 --> 00:36:19,320
Then why,

824
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:19,920
knowing her situation, are you discharging her?

825
00:36:23,159 --> 00:36:24,320
I personally explained

826
00:36:24,599 --> 00:36:25,440
the surgical plan and risks

827
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,079
to the family.

828
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,280
They don't want surgery.

829
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,159
What else can I do?

830
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:30,320
You can talk to them.

831
00:36:30,679 --> 00:36:31,639
You can persuade them.

832
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:32,239
Yu...

833
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:33,679
Director.

834
00:36:34,199 --> 00:36:34,719
Please sign this.

835
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:36,760
Director Lin.

836
00:36:39,519 --> 00:36:39,960
Thank you.

837
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,000
Given Yu Aizhu's condition,

838
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:49,840
no matter how hesitant her family is,

839
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,000
you shouldn't give up on her.

840
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:52,880
I haven't given up.

841
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,079
If they agree to surgery,

842
00:36:54,119 --> 00:36:55,480
I can schedule it immediately.

843
00:36:56,159 --> 00:36:56,920
But her family

844
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:57,840
has chosen conservative treatment.

845
00:36:58,119 --> 00:36:59,199
Then she should transfer

846
00:36:59,239 --> 00:37:00,000
to a lower-level hospital or community facility.

847
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,360
Beds are extremely tight.

848
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:02,159
Of course they should be reserved

849
00:37:02,199 --> 00:37:02,960
for patients who need them more.

850
00:37:03,199 --> 00:37:04,239
Yu Aizhu is exactly

851
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,480
a patient who needs one.

852
00:37:13,039 --> 00:37:13,920
Director Lin.

853
00:37:14,639 --> 00:37:15,079
Go ahead.

854
00:37:15,719 --> 00:37:16,800
Director Zhou,

855
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:18,119
the patient with recurrent ventricular tachycardia—

856
00:37:18,119 --> 00:37:18,880
his family is here.

857
00:37:19,559 --> 00:37:20,320
Ask them to wait a moment.

858
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:20,920
I'll be right there.

859
00:37:21,559 --> 00:37:21,920
Okay.

860
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:25,400
You can't leave.

861
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:27,760
What else do you want me to say?

862
00:37:28,199 --> 00:37:29,559
Yu Aizhu's case is special.

863
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:30,599
Her husband

864
00:37:30,599 --> 00:37:31,519
is also in poor health.

865
00:37:31,559 --> 00:37:32,440
Their son isn't nearby.

866
00:37:32,639 --> 00:37:33,559
If you send her home

867
00:37:33,599 --> 00:37:34,480
and she has an episode there,

868
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:34,800
what will they do?

869
00:37:35,039 --> 00:37:36,480
I know their situation is difficult.

870
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,039
But if she suddenly deteriorates,

871
00:37:38,119 --> 00:37:38,639
as unfortunate as that would be,

872
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:39,519
she'll have to come through the ER.

873
00:37:42,519 --> 00:37:43,000
Zhou Xiaofeng.

874
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:44,599
Are you really that busy?

875
00:37:49,679 --> 00:37:50,679
I really am.

876
00:37:51,039 --> 00:37:51,800
And you heard it yourself.

877
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:52,840
A family is waiting to speak with me.

878
00:37:53,199 --> 00:37:53,960
Do you remember

879
00:37:54,559 --> 00:37:55,519
Hua'er two years ago?

880
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,400
How long did he stay here?

881
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:58,960
More than two years.

882
00:37:59,199 --> 00:37:59,639
Aunt Yu

883
00:37:59,679 --> 00:38:00,280
has only been here two weeks,

884
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,000
and you're already forcing her out.

885
00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:01,800
Hua'er's case

886
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:02,639
was completely different.

887
00:38:03,039 --> 00:38:03,960
He had no one.

888
00:38:04,119 --> 00:38:05,239
He qualified as an elderly person without family

889
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:06,400
and received government assistance.

890
00:38:06,519 --> 00:38:07,280
Yu Aizhu doesn't.

891
00:38:07,559 --> 00:38:08,000
She has a family.

892
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:08,440
We can't

893
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,360
keep her here indefinitely.

894
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:10,480
Don't give me

895
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:11,039
all that bureaucratic nonsense.

896
00:38:11,039 --> 00:38:11,920
You're simply

897
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:12,840
cherry-picking patients.

898
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,119
How am I cherry-picking?

899
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,840
You came in and started accusing me,

900
00:38:16,159 --> 00:38:17,079
as if I were pushing the patient

901
00:38:17,119 --> 00:38:18,039
toward certain death.

902
00:38:18,119 --> 00:38:19,000
What exactly did I do wrong?

903
00:38:25,239 --> 00:38:26,039
Hello, Zhang Zhen.

904
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,760
Dr. Fang, are you busy?

905
00:38:28,519 --> 00:38:28,960
Go ahead.

906
00:38:29,360 --> 00:38:30,239
How many times must I say it?

907
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,320
They don't want surgery,

908
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,039
and beds are tight.

909
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,280
I'm under pressure too.

910
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,480
Everyone alive is under pressure.

911
00:38:34,519 --> 00:38:35,400
Your pressure matters,

912
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:35,960
but the patient's

913
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:36,880
doesn't?

914
00:38:37,039 --> 00:38:37,480
It does.

915
00:38:37,639 --> 00:38:38,320
And when we're under pressure,

916
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:40,039
we should follow rules.

917
00:38:40,159 --> 00:38:40,840
The hospital's rules,

918
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:42,000
or your rules for doing business?

919
00:38:42,199 --> 00:38:42,880
What did you say?

920
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:43,559
Enough.

921
00:38:43,559 --> 00:38:44,320
Patients are just money-making machines to you.

922
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:45,320
Are you accusing me? Enough.

923
00:38:45,639 --> 00:38:46,440
Stop.

924
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:48,559
Lin Yi.

925
00:38:49,559 --> 00:38:50,880
Your brother has his difficulties too.

926
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,599
Every department has to consider

927
00:38:53,639 --> 00:38:55,039
bed turnover.

928
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,639
Especially a top-tier hospital like ours.

929
00:38:56,679 --> 00:38:57,639
Don't bother reasoning with him.

930
00:38:59,280 --> 00:38:59,840
Director Lin

931
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,159
has been protected all his life.

932
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:02,360
He knows nothing of real-world constraints,

933
00:39:02,559 --> 00:39:03,480
so he can act on impulse

934
00:39:03,599 --> 00:39:04,480
and do whatever he wants.

935
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:05,400
Brother.

936
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,760
Hasn't he always been this way?

937
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:08,159
He only thinks about treating patients.

938
00:39:08,239 --> 00:39:09,400
He may not consider

939
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,320
everything else thoroughly.

940
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:11,519
He needs to grow up.

941
00:39:13,159 --> 00:39:14,519
How long will you keep acting on impulse

942
00:39:15,639 --> 00:39:16,480
and making everyone around you

943
00:39:16,519 --> 00:39:17,840
worry and clean up after you?

944
00:39:21,480 --> 00:39:21,840
Fine.

945
00:39:25,159 --> 00:39:25,679
Grow up?

946
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:28,880
You're the leader.

947
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:30,360
You're so busy.

948
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:31,639
If you won't take her,

949
00:39:32,199 --> 00:39:32,679
I will.

950
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:35,840
Lin Yi.

951
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:45,840
Brother.

952
00:39:47,559 --> 00:39:48,960
Don't be angry with him.

953
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,679
I'll talk to him again.

954
00:39:54,639 --> 00:39:55,400
Why are you here?

955
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,840
I was just passing by

956
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,360
and heard you arguing.

957
00:40:03,119 --> 00:40:04,519
Someone asked you to mediate, didn't they?

958
00:40:09,079 --> 00:40:10,239
You have your own work.

959
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:12,039
You don't always need

960
00:40:12,079 --> 00:40:13,039
to be our peacemaker.

961
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:15,400
But if I hadn't come,

962
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,199
how far would this fight have gone?

963
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:18,280
So what?

964
00:40:18,559 --> 00:40:19,880
That's between him and me.

965
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,400
You don't have to understand everyone.

966
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,480
No one is born

967
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:27,400
to be a little sun,

968
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,559
always warming and lighting others.

969
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,400
She's transferring from Cardiology?

970
00:40:32,280 --> 00:40:32,639
Yes.

971
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,719
Are you confident

972
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:36,280
you can persuade the family within three days?

973
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:37,159
I...

974
00:40:38,880 --> 00:40:40,360
I can try.

975
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,000
It's better than doing nothing.

976
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,119
Is the patient someone you know?

977
00:40:44,719 --> 00:40:45,159
No.

978
00:40:45,639 --> 00:40:46,760
I met her during a consultation.

979
00:40:48,039 --> 00:40:48,679
But the elderly woman's

980
00:40:48,719 --> 00:40:49,719
condition is very poor.

981
00:40:50,119 --> 00:40:51,480
Cardiology was sending her home.

982
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:52,840
I couldn't stand by,

983
00:40:53,199 --> 00:40:53,960
so I brought her

984
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:54,639
to our department.

985
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:56,239
Cardiology

986
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:56,880
doesn't perform as many

987
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:58,000
Category IV surgeries as we do.

988
00:40:58,599 --> 00:40:59,599
Their reimbursement ceiling is lower,

989
00:41:00,239 --> 00:41:01,679
so they rely on profitable patients.

990
00:41:02,039 --> 00:41:02,920
I imagine Director Zhou

991
00:41:03,199 --> 00:41:04,559
was thinking along those lines.

992
00:41:05,559 --> 00:41:06,519
Thinking what?

993
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,199
A doctor's job is to save lives.

994
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,159
How can patients be good or bad?

995
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,199
You could see it

996
00:41:13,199 --> 00:41:14,079
from what happened with Xuemei.

997
00:41:14,079 --> 00:41:14,840
Director Zhou

998
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:15,920
is extremely

999
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,079
career-driven.

1000
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:18,639
Especially now that he's in management.

1001
00:41:18,719 --> 00:41:19,480
I can understand him even more.

1002
00:41:20,639 --> 00:41:21,360
You're the one

1003
00:41:22,519 --> 00:41:23,840
who can be too emotional.

1004
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:24,960
That's not good.

1005
00:41:28,679 --> 00:41:29,480
All right, let's go.

1006
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:39,000
Handle the transfer paperwork.

1007
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:41,119
I'll find a bed.

1008
00:41:46,599 --> 00:41:47,559
You agreed, Director?

1009
00:41:48,159 --> 00:41:48,760
That's wonderful.

1010
00:41:49,199 --> 00:41:49,639
Then

1011
00:41:49,679 --> 00:41:50,800
I'll tell them right away.

1012
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:51,840
Transfer her under my care.

1013
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:52,880
Anything else?

1014
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:06,039
You're going to bankrupt this department.

1015
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:07,679
The wheelchair is here.

1016
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,039
Sister Yalan,

1017
00:42:11,239 --> 00:42:12,360
the humidifier water is empty.

1018
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:13,239
Later, replace it

1019
00:42:13,239 --> 00:42:13,920
along with her nasal cannula.

1020
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:14,599
Okay.

1021
00:42:18,320 --> 00:42:19,519
No. I don't want to go home. What's wrong?

1022
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:20,639
No, no.

1023
00:42:20,719 --> 00:42:21,199
What's wrong?

1024
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:22,599
Save me.

1025
00:42:24,159 --> 00:42:24,639
Save me, Mom.

1026
00:42:24,800 --> 00:42:25,920
Mom, we're not going home.

1027
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:28,320
We're going to Cardiac Surgery.

1028
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,000
Not home.

1029
00:42:29,039 --> 00:42:30,159
Don't be afraid, Mom.

1030
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:31,320
Save me.

1031
00:42:32,039 --> 00:42:33,559
Let her keep it on for now,

1032
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:34,519
and change it when we get there.

1033
00:42:34,679 --> 00:42:35,039
Okay.

1034
00:42:36,239 --> 00:42:36,760
Don't change it.

1035
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:38,079
We won't take it off.

1036
00:42:38,119 --> 00:42:39,519
Okay, okay.

1037
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:40,360
Well...

1038
00:42:41,079 --> 00:42:42,039
Don't be afraid, Mom.

1039
00:42:42,639 --> 00:42:43,280
We're just...

1040
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:43,920
Okay.

1041
00:42:44,079 --> 00:42:44,920
Hold this.

1042
00:42:45,159 --> 00:42:45,679
Mom.

1043
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:47,320
We're only changing rooms.

1044
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:47,960
There's nothing to fear.

1045
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:48,480
Come on, Mom.

1046
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:49,920
Let's put your shoes on. Careful.

1047
00:42:51,639 --> 00:42:52,639
Come on, Mom.

1048
00:42:52,679 --> 00:42:53,280
Have you signed everything?
